    {
      "instruction": "<p>Tear your <strong>ciabatta[s]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>into rough, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the<strong> torn ciabatta</strong> to a baking tray with your <strong>toasted sesame oil</strong>, <strong>black sesame seeds</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 5 min or until golden and crisp – these are your<strong> sesame croutons</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1634748184417-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1634748184417-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1634748184417-x700.jpg",
